":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-extensions","content":"Provides support for HTML, useful if you are working with NUI."},"41":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-22","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-settings","content":"Git Blame"},"42":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-23","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-settings","content":"Diagnostics (Like ErrorLens)"},"43":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-24","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-settings","content":"Lua Language Server Settings"},"44":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-25","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-settings","content":"We Highly recommend using per-project configs via `.luarc.json` files. You can read how to setup the fivem-lls-addon here"},"45":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-26","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#visual-studio-code","content":"Visual Studio Code is the most popular IDE, however its much slower than Zed, takes up more resources and requires more extensions to have a proper developer experience. I'd highly recommend switching to and/or using Zed instead."},"46":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-27","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-extensions-1","content":"Lua Language Server by sumneko"},"47":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-28","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-extensions-1","content":"Adds proper lua syntax highlighting and support for the Lua Language Server (LLS)"},"48":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-29","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-extensions-1","content":"Error Lens by Alexander"},"49":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-30","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-extensions-1","content":"In-line hightlighting of error, warning and other language diagnostics"},"50":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-31","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-extensions-1","content":"TODO Highlight by Wayou Liu"},"51":{"id":"/docs/tips/ide-32","page_id":"/docs/tips/ide","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/ide#recommended-extensions-1","content":"Highlight TODOs, FIXMEs, and any keywords, annotations..."},"52":{"id":"/docs/tips","page_id":"/docs/tips","type":"page","content":"Tips & Tricks","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Getting Started","Tips & Tricks"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/tips"},"53":{"id":"/docs/tips-0","page_id":"/docs/tips","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"The Best Tip"},"54":{"id":"/docs/tips-1","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"The best tip we can possibly provide you is **do not make asking for help your first step, instead make it your last**."},"55":{"id":"/docs/tips-2","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Before reaching out for support, take the time to:"},"56":{"id":"/docs/tips-3","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Read the documentation thouroughly to be sure you didn't miss something."},"57":{"id":"/docs/tips-4","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Double or even triple check the installation instructions."},"58":{"id":"/docs/tips-5","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Look through frequently asked questions"},"59":{"id":"/docs/tips-6","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Read the actual error you're getting, it might be overwhelming but error messages are usually there to help you and tell you whats happening."},"60":{"id":"/docs/tips-7","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Search google, youtube, github, community forums etc to see if someone has had the same issue as you."},"61":{"id":"/docs/tips-8","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"More often than not, the answer to your problem is already available. Spending a few minutes researching your problem can save both you and others a lot of time."},"62":{"id":"/docs/tips-9","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"More importantly, try and understand *why* something works instead of only learning *how* to make something work. Every bug, error message, and unexpected behavior is an oppourtunity to learn."},"63":{"id":"/docs/tips-10","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Ask yourself questions like:"},"64":{"id":"/docs/tips-11","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Why is this variable `nil`?"},"65":{"id":"/docs/tips-12","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Why is this function returning an error?"},"66":{"id":"/docs/tips-13","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Where is this event being triggered?"},"67":{"id":"/docs/tips-14","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"What data is this function expecting?"},"68":{"id":"/docs/tips-15","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"What changed that caused this to stop working?"},"69":{"id":"/docs/tips-16","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Developers improve by being curious, the more you investigate problems yourself the easier it becomes to solve future issues without needing to ask for help. That being said, there is nothing wrong with asking for help when you need it."},"70":{"id":"/docs/tips-17","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Give yourself 15-30 minutes to genuinely investigate a problem before asking for help. If you're still stuck after that, ask away - but be sure to explain what you've already tried. It shows others that you've put in the effort, and makes it much easier for them to help you."},"71":{"id":"/docs/tips-18","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"A question that includes \"Here's exactly what I expected to happen vs what is actually happening, and here's what i've tried so far...\" is much more likely to get a useful answer than \"x doesn't work\"."},"72":{"id":"/docs/tips-19","page_id":"/docs/tips","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips#the-best-tip","content":"Finally, Google and YouTube are your friends, learning how to search effectively is one of the most valuable skills any developer can have. No developer knows every function available in whatever language/system they're working with, developers reference existing content and ask questions constantly - it's part of being a developer."},"73":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","type":"page","content":"Organizing Projects","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Getting Started","Tips & Tricks"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/tips/organization"},"74":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-0","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/tips/organization#organizing-resources","content":"Organizing Resources"},"75":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-1","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/tips/organization#organizing-your-server","content":"Organizing Your Server"},"76":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-2","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/tips/organization#there-is-no-correct-way","content":"There is no \"correct\" way"},"77":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-3","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/organization","content":"Keeping your projects organized is very important. Whether it be a resource or the server itself, here are some tips we have on how to keep your stuff clean and organized."},"78":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-4","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/organization#organizing-resources","content":"Most beginners will just toss client & server files into a directory with an `fxmanifest.lua` and call it good. This makes expanding resources much harder than it needs to be, especially for those of a large size. This is how we personally structure our resources to ensure clean and maintainable code:"},"79":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-5","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/organization#organizing-resources","content":"We have a resource template available here if you wish to use the same format we do."},"80":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-6","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/organization#organizing-resources","content":"<File name=\"module_one.lua\" />"},"81":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-7","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/organization#organizing-resources","content":"<File name=\"module_two.lua\" />"},"82":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-8","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/organization#organizing-resources","content":"<File name=\"main.lua\" />"},"83":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-9","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/organization#organizing-resources","content":"<File name=\"utils.lua\" />"},"84":{"id":"/docs/tips/organization-10","page_id":"/docs/tips/organization","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/tips/organization#organizing-resources","content":"<File name=\"module_one.lua\" />"},"85":{"id":"/d