 config file is found in `data/config_evidence.lua` and contains all of the configuration for evidence."},"299":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-14","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#locker-room-configuration","content":"The locker room configuration consists of two different files, the outfits located in `data/data_outfits.lua` and the configuration located in `data/config_outfits.lua`"},"300":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-15","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#locker-room-configuration","content":"Configuration:"},"301":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-16","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#locker-room-configuration","content":"Outfits:"},"302":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-17","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#locker-room-configuration","content":"You can quickly get your current outfit by running the command `/getclothing`, this will copy it to your clipboard so you can paste it here."},"303":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-18","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#shotspotter-configuration","content":"The shotspotter configuration can be found in the `data/config_shotspotter.lua` file."},"304":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-19","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#armory-configuration","content":"The armory config file can be found in `data/data_armories.lua`. You can quickly get your current loadout by running `/getloadout`, this will copy the information to your clipboard to paste into the file."},"305":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-20","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#armory-configuration","content":"In order for addon weapons to work with the `/getloadout` command, you need to add them to `data/data_weapons.lua` and their components if they have any to `data/data_components.lua`"},"306":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-21","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#object-configuration","content":"The object list configuration file can be found in `data/data_objects.lua`."},"307":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-22","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#ped-configuration","content":"The ped configuration file can be found in `data/data_peds.lua` and includes all of the duty peds or alert peds."},"308":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-23","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#garage-configuration","content":"The garage configuration file can be found in `data/data_garages.lua` and includes all of the garages & their vehicles."},"309":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-24","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#garage-configuration","content":"You can copy your current vehicles information to your clipboard to paste it in this file via the command `/getvehprops`"},"310":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-25","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#bridge--integration-configuration","content":"All of the framework and resource integrations can be found in the `bridge` directory, we expect you to have atleast a basic understanding of Lua & how to integrate with other resources to edit these. Minimal support will be provided. If you have anything you want to recommend we integrate with, please let us know and we'll try our best to add it!"},"311":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-26","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#locals--language","content":"All of the respective language/locales & command names can be changed in the `locales` directory."},"312":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration-27","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/configuration","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/paid/police/configuration#locals--language","content":"Users can set their language via the `/ox_lib` command in-game if its enabled. If the language file doesn't exist, it defaults to English."},"313":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/developers","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/developers","type":"page","content":"Developers","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Resources","Paid","Complete Police System"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/paid/police/developers"},"314":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/developers-0","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/developers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/paid/police/developers#complete-police-system---developer-documentation","content":"Complete Police System - Developer Documentation"},"315":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/developers-1","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/developers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/paid/police/developers#events","content":"Events"},"316":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/developers-2","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/developers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/paid/police/developers#searchplayer","content":"`searchPlayer`"},"317":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/developers-3","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/developers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/paid/police/developers#escortplayer","content":"`escortPlayer`"},"318":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/developers-4","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/developers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/paid/police/developers#spawnobjectitem","content":"`spawnObject(item)`"},"319":{"id":"/docs/paid/police/developers-5","page_id":"/docs/paid/police/developers","type":"heading","tags":[],