ers can create groups and invite their friends to participate in jobs with them."],[263,"💰 Custom Rewards & Payouts: Add item drops, cash bonuses, or rarity-based loot pools per zone."],[375,"💸 Fines System: Issue configurable monetary penalties."],[365,"📍 Duty Blips: Identify active officers on the map based on department duty status."],[370,"📸 ALPR Integration: Automatically detect and flag vehicle license plates."],[363,"📹 Live Body Cameras: Real-time officer bodycam functionality."],[264,"🔁 Zone Cooldowns: Prevent repetitive routes and encourage players to explore the map."],[358,"🔊 ShotSpotter Integration: Automatically detect and report nearby gunfire activity."],[366,"🔍 Frisking & Searching: Immersive search mechanics with animations."],[357,"🔗 Cuffing & Zipties: Multiple restraint types with animations and configurable behavior."],[354,"🔫 Advanced Police Armory: Configurable weapon and equipment distribution system."],[360,"🕶️ Tint Meter Tool: Measure and enforce vehicle window tint limits."],[369,"🗄️ Department Facilities: Personal lockers and boss management menus."],[261,"🗺️ Dynamic Zone System: Automatically assigns random zones based on cooldowns, distance, and truck capability."],[374,"🤼 Tackle Mechanic: Physically stop fleeing suspects."],[266,"🧩 Fully Configurable: All data-driven via easily editable config and zone files."],[364,"🧪 Evidence System: Collect and analyze casings, blood samples, GSR, BAC and fingerprints."],[361,"🧬 Fingerprint Reader: Capture and analyze fingerprint evidence from suspects and scenes."],[359,"🙌 Hands Up System: Player surrender mechanic with animation support."],[353,"🚓 Police Vehicle Garage: Department-managed fleet system with vehicle tracking and return logic."],[371,"🚚 AI Tow Service: Request AI tow trucks with impound functionality."],[259,"🚛 Truck-Based Progression: Trash collection is tied directly to the truck, not the player - perfect for multi-person crews."],[376,"🚦 Opticom Integration: Automatically control traffic lights during emergency response."],[362,"🚧 Placeable Police Objects: Deploy cones, barriers, spike strips and more."],[373,"🚨 Panic Button: Emergency distress alert system for officers."],[137,"A function generally should do one thing. Instead of creating one large function that handles multiple responsibilities like `SpawnVehicle()`, break it up into smaller functions like `LoadModel()`, `CreateVehicle()`, `SetupVehicle()`, `GetVehicleKeys()`. Smaller functions are easier to read, test, debug and can be reused instead of rewriting the same code a dozen times."],[71,"A question that includes \"Here's exactly what I expected to happen vs what is actually happening, and here's what i've tried so far...\" is much more likely to get a useful answer than \"x doesn't work\"."],[413,"Add the items from `_INSTALL/items/items.lua` to your `ox_inventory/data/items.lua` & the images from `_INSTALL/items/images` to the `ox_inventory/web/images` directory."],[402,"Add the resources to your server.cfg (or resources.cfg)"],[395,"Additional feedback and testing by Scorpion, NovaMonkey, and other community members."],[47,"Adds proper lua syntax highlighting and support for the Lua Language Server (LLS)"],[238,"Adds trash to the trucks current zone, if the maxCollection amount is reached it will assign a new zone."],[216,"addTrashToTruck"],[209,"addTrashToZone"],[179,"Advanced Fuel System"],[252,"Advanced Garbage Job"],[175,"Airdrops"],[278,"All credit for included vehicles goes to original authors - Monkeypolice188, Rockstar Games, Weeby, Fenton, Compeast, Dexyfex and the CodeWalker Team, Eddlm, w\\.., (Ambient), Lorify: The Workshop Team"],[341,"All of the bridge files are located in `bridge` directory. This requires decent knowledge of the lua scripting language and how FiveM works. This is mostly unsupported."],[184,"All of the configuration & data files have detailed comments explaining how to configure everything to your liking, if you need assistance please reach out t