ean, organized and readable code. Here's some more resources for you to reference:"],[293,"Garage Configuration"],[251,"Garbage Job"],[203,"getPlayerTruck"],[235,"Gets a trucks config information from its model."],[206,"getTruckConfigData"],[41,"Git Blame"],[29,"Git Firefly by d1y"],[12,"Git is a very powerful version control tool that should be used whether you're just making a server or developing resources. Popular implementations include `Github`, `GitLab` and `BitBucket` - the most common you'll run into is `Github` as it is the most popular and in my opinion, the best option in most cases."],[15,"Git's official website"],[14,"Github's Guide to setting up Git"],[70,"Give yourself 15-30 minutes to genuinely investigate a problem before asking for help. If you're still stuck after that, ask away - but be sure to explain what you've already tried. It shows others that you've put in the effort, and makes it much easier for them to help you."],[205,"giveRandomItemReward"],[234,"Gives an item reward to player based on zone loot table"],[135,"Good"],[140,"Good"],[144,"Good"],[148,"Good"],[151,"Good"],[149,"Good comments will explain *why* something is happening, not *what* is happening. People reading your code should be able to understand *what* is happening just by reading it."],[207,"handleDeposit"],[204,"handlePayout"],[233,"Handles payout distribution and cleans up truck."],[236,"Handles the deposit refund logic when a truck is returned."],[281,"Heli Crash"],[222,"Here you will find a basic list of how you can modify our resource if you are a developer. This assumes you have *at minimum* basic knowledge of how FiveM programming works and the lua scripting language."],[329,"Here you will find a basic list of how you can modify our resource if you are a developer. This assumes you have *at minimum* basic knowledge of how FiveM programming works and the lua scripting language."],[419,"Here's a list basic troubleshooting steps for TAM\\_Police."],[27,"Here's a list o