upport for XML/Meta files. This is useful if you are working with those files."],[59,"Read the actual error you're getting, it might be overwhelming but error messages are usually there to help you and tell you whats happening."],[56,"Read the documentation thouroughly to be sure you didn't miss something."],[21,"Recommended Extensions"],[24,"Recommended Extensions"],[22,"Recommended Settings"],[128,"Remove Dead Code"],[218,"resetOutfit"],[247,"Resets a peds outfit back to their previous one, if able."],[340,"Resets the hands up status of the specified ped."],[424,"Resource must be named TAM\\_Police to function properly! Aborting loadup."],[417,"Resource Startup Errors"],[232,"Return player's truck. If ownerOnly true, return only if player is owner"],[335,"Returns a boolean on wether the ped is cuffed or not."],[214,"returnTruck"],[257,"SCFD GarbageJob is a fully dynamic and performance-optimized garbage collection job for FiveM, designed for realism, replay-ability, and server economy integration."],[348,"SCFD Police System is a fully modular, performance-optimized law enforcement framework for FiveM, designed to provide immersive policing mechanics while remaining flexible for any server style."],[200,"scfd_garbagejob:clockIn"],[201,"scfd_garbagejob:clockOut"],[197,"scfd_garbagejob:fetchTruck"],[198,"scfd_garbagejob:fetchTruckData"],[199,"scfd_garbagejob:returnTruck"],[60,"Search google, youtube, github, community forums etc to see if someone has had the same issue as you."],[217,"setOutfit"],[246,"Sets a peds outfit"],[289,"Shotspotter Configuration"],[38,"Shows colors directly in the editor, like HEX or RGB."],[170,"Simple Bug Reports"],[171,"Simple Changelog System"],[172,"Simple Chat Toolbox"],[177,"Simple Elevator System"],[173,"Simple Tackle System"],[136,"Someone reading your code shouldn't have to guess what `p` or `c` actually means."],[333,"Spawn an object from the object list.\n`item` string name from `data/data_objects.lua`"],[31,"SQL by nervenes, notpeter, phileix and tammyxiong"],[32,"SQL language support, this is useful if you are working with SQL files."],[221,"Statebags"],[274,"Support Discord"],[391,"Support Discord"],[268,"Supports any\\* inventory, target system, notifications, progressbars & skillchecks."],[385,"Supports any\\* inventory, target system, notifications, progressbars & skillchecks."],[277,"Thanks to xthrasherrr, scorpionong, novamonkey, and various members of the qbox discord for ideas & feedback."],[304,"The armory config file can be found in `data/data_armories.lua`. You can quickly get your current loadout by running `/getloadout`, this will copy the information to your clipboard to paste into the file."],[53,"The Best Tip"],[54,"The best tip we can possibly provide you is **do not make asking for help your first step, instead make it your last**."],[435,"The bridge module has been messed up or is missing. Please download the latest release from the CFX Portal and replace the `modules/bridge` directory."],[437,"The custom sound effects were unable to load. Please download the latest release from the CFX Portal and replace the `audiodata` and `audiodirectory` directories."],[298,"The evidence config file is found in `data/config_evidence.lua` and contains all of the configuration for evidence."],[119,"The exact folder names don't matter. What's important is that you choose a structure that makes sense to you and stay consistent. If every vehicle lives in one place, every map in another, and every script has a logical home, maintaining your server becomes significantly easier as it grows."],[431,"The file `locales/en.json` is missing! This is required. If you wish to add more languages, please read this."],[308,"The garage configuration file can be found in `data/data_garages.lua` and includes all of the garages & their vehicles."],[186,"The locations data file is located at `data/locations.lua` and handles all of the location-specific information like ped locations, return points, etc"],