hat is Next?"],[162,"Whenever you're working in a file, look for small improvements you can make. Maybe that's renaming a confusing variable, removing unused code, improving a comment or something else. Small improvements add up over time and make your project much easier to maintain."],[66,"Where is this event being triggered?"],[160,"While this sounds counter productive, focus on writing readable and functioning code before micro optimizations. Write code that works, profile it, and *then* optimize the parts that actually need it."],[65,"Why is this function returning an error?"],[64,"Why is this variable `nil`?"],[283,"World Interactions"],[132,"Writing code that *works* is only half the battle. Writing code that's easy to read, understand and modify months later is what separates a good developer from a great one. As your project grows, you'll find yourself spending far more time reading and maintaining existing code than writing new code. These practices make that experience much more enjoyable, for both yourself and anybody else that works on your project."],[120,"Writing Maintainable Code"],[418,"X feature isn't working!"],[35,"XML by sweetppro"],[439,"You are missing the respective dependency. Please read this"],[309,"You can copy your current vehicles information to your clipboard to paste it in this file via the command `/getvehprops`"],[302,"You can quickly get your current outfit by running the command `/getclothing`, this will copy it to your clipboard so you can paste it here."],[250,"You can view available states in `shared/const.lua` in the `CONST.STATES` table."],[427,"You have modified the fxmanifest.lua file and removed certain required fields. Please download the latest release from the CFX Portal and replace the fxmanifest.lua file."],[425,"You have renamed the resource. Please ensure that the resource name is exactly `TAM_Police` or else it wont work. This is cAsE sEnSiTiVe"],[429,"You messed up the `data/configuration.lua` file. This is usuall